      "rawMarkdown": "# 64. Antipathy\n\n**Pronunciation:** an-TIP-ə-thee\n**Part of speech:** Noun\n**Core meaning:** A strong feeling of dislike, hostility, or opposition.\n**Bangla meaning:** তীব্র বিরাগ, ঘৃণা, বিদ্বেষ, অপছন্দ\n**Root story:** From Greek **anti-** = against + **pathos** = feeling. Antipathy literally means “feeling against.”\n**Simple explanation:** Antipathy is stronger than simple dislike. It suggests deep emotional opposition.\n**Memory hook:** **Anti + pathy = feeling against someone/something.**\n**GRE synonyms:** aversion, hostility, animosity, enmity, antagonism\n**Basic synonyms:** dislike, hatred, opposition, resentment\n**Antonyms:** sympathy, affection, fondness, liking, goodwill\n**Common usage:** deep antipathy, personal antipathy, political antipathy, antipathy toward authority\n**Confusing word:** **Antipathy ≠ Apathy.** Antipathy = strong dislike; apathy = no feeling or interest.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. He felt antipathy toward liars.\n   Meaning: He strongly disliked liars.\n   Bangla: মিথ্যাবাদীদের প্রতি বিরাগ।\n\n2. Her antipathy was obvious.\n   Meaning: Her dislike was clear.\n   Bangla: ঘৃণা স্পষ্ট ছিল।\n\n3. The two neighbors had mutual antipathy.\n   Meaning: They disliked each other.\n   Bangla: পারস্পরিক বিরাগ।\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n4. The senator’s antipathy toward regulation shaped his economic policy.\n   Meaning: His strong dislike of regulation influenced his decisions.\n   Bangla: নিয়ন্ত্রণের প্রতি বিরাগ।\n\n5. The critic’s antipathy to modern art made his review predictable.\n   Meaning: His strong dislike affected his judgment.\n   Bangla: আধুনিক শিল্পের প্রতি অপছন্দ।\n\n6. Years of rivalry created deep antipathy between the two institutions.\n   Meaning: Long conflict produced hostility.\n   Bangla: গভীর বিদ্বেষ।\n\n7. The reform failed partly because of public antipathy toward higher taxes.\n   Meaning: People strongly opposed higher taxes.\n   Bangla: কর বৃদ্ধির প্রতি বিরাগ।\n\n**Real-world / paper-style examples**\n\n8. In political analysis, antipathy toward elites can shape voting behavior.\n   Meaning: Strong dislike can influence political choices.\n   Bangla: অভিজাতদের প্রতি বিরাগ।\n\n9. In organizational studies, employee antipathy toward management may reduce cooperation.\n   Meaning: Hostility harms teamwork.\n   Bangla: ব্যবস্থাপনার প্রতি বিরাগ।\n\n10. In social psychology, antipathy can develop from repeated negative contact between groups.\n    Meaning: Repeated bad experience can create hostility.\n    Bangla: বারবার খারাপ অভিজ্ঞতায় বিরাগ তৈরি হয়।\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. She had an **aversion** to public praise.\n2. The negotiations failed because of mutual **hostility**.\n3. His **animosity** toward the rival party was obvious.\n4. The long war created deep **enmity** between the nations.\n5. The policy generated strong **antagonism** among workers.\n6. The patient had an **aversion** to bitter medicine.\n7. The speech increased **hostility** rather than reducing it.\n8. Personal **animosity** clouded his judgment.\n9. The tribes’ historical **enmity** complicated peace talks.\n10. Her reforms faced **antagonism** from conservative officials.\n11. He expressed an **aversion** to unnecessary risk.\n12. Public **hostility** grew after the scandal.\n13. The article revealed the author’s **animosity** toward industrialization.\n14. Centuries of **enmity** could not be erased quickly.\n15. The proposal met fierce **antagonism** from local residents.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Antipathy = feeling against = তীব্র বিরাগ**\n\n---",
