      "rawMarkdown": "# 65. Arcane\n\n**Pronunciation:** ar-KAYN\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Secret, mysterious, or understood by only a few people.\n**Bangla meaning:** গুপ্ত, রহস্যময়, দুর্বোধ্য, অল্প কয়েকজনের জানা\n**Root story:** From Latin **arcanus**, meaning secret or hidden, related to **arca**, a chest or box. Imagine knowledge locked inside a hidden chest.\n**Simple explanation:** Arcane knowledge is not common knowledge. It is specialized, mysterious, or difficult for ordinary people to understand.\n**Memory hook:** **Arcane = knowledge locked in a secret box.**\n**GRE synonyms:** esoteric, obscure, mysterious, cryptic, abstruse\n**Basic synonyms:** secret, hidden, difficult, specialized\n**Antonyms:** common, obvious, familiar, accessible, clear\n**Common usage:** arcane rules, arcane rituals, arcane knowledge, arcane legal language\n**Confusing word:** **Arcane ≠ Archaic.** Arcane = mysterious/secret; archaic = old-fashioned.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. The book was full of arcane symbols.\n   Meaning: The symbols were mysterious.\n   Bangla: রহস্যময় চিহ্ন।\n\n2. He studied arcane traditions.\n   Meaning: He studied secret or little-known traditions.\n   Bangla: গুপ্ত ঐতিহ্য।\n\n3. The rule seemed arcane to beginners.\n   Meaning: Beginners could not understand it easily.\n   Bangla: নতুনদের কাছে দুর্বোধ্য।\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n4. The professor explained an arcane theory in simple language.\n   Meaning: The theory was difficult and specialized.\n   Bangla: জটিল তত্ত্ব।\n\n5. The legal document contained arcane terminology that confused the public.\n   Meaning: The terms were difficult and specialized.\n   Bangla: দুর্বোধ্য আইনগত শব্দ।\n\n6. The committee rejected the proposal because it depended on arcane technical assumptions.\n   Meaning: The assumptions were too specialized and hard to verify.\n   Bangla: বিশেষজ্ঞ ছাড়া বোঝা কঠিন।\n\n7. What appeared arcane to outsiders was routine knowledge among specialists.\n   Meaning: It was mysterious only to non-experts.\n   Bangla: অ-বিশেষজ্ঞদের কাছে রহস্যময়।\n\n**Real-world / paper-style examples**\n\n8. In computer security, arcane details of encryption can determine system safety.\n   Meaning: Specialized hidden details matter.\n   Bangla: এনক্রিপশনের জটিল বিষয়।\n\n9. In historical research, scholars often decode arcane manuscripts to understand lost traditions.\n   Meaning: Old specialized texts require expert interpretation.\n   Bangla: গুপ্ত পাণ্ডুলিপি।\n\n10. In tax law, arcane regulations can make compliance difficult for small businesses.\n    Meaning: Complex rules are hard to follow.\n    Bangla: দুর্বোধ্য করনীতি।\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The ritual was too **esoteric** for outsiders to understand.\n2. The poem’s meaning remained **obscure**.\n3. The cave painting had a **mysterious** purpose.\n4. His reply was **cryptic**, leaving everyone confused.\n5. The philosopher used **abstruse** arguments.\n6. The lecture on quantum fields was **esoteric**.\n7. The origin of the custom is **obscure**.\n8. The scientist investigated a **mysterious** signal.\n9. The note was so **cryptic** that nobody knew what to do.\n10. The article was **abstruse** even for graduate students.\n11. The group preserved **esoteric** teachings.\n12. The historian found **obscure** references in old archives.\n13. The cause of the disease remained **mysterious**.\n14. His **cryptic** warning became clear only later.\n15. The manual was filled with **abstruse** formulas.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Arcane = hidden specialist knowledge = গুপ্ত / দুর্বোধ্য**\n\n---",
