      "rawMarkdown": "# 66. Arduous\n\n**Pronunciation:** AR-joo-əs\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Very difficult and requiring great effort.\n**Bangla meaning:** কঠিন, পরিশ্রমসাধ্য, শ্রমসাধ্য\n**Root story:** From Latin **arduus**, meaning high, steep, or difficult. Imagine climbing a steep mountain.\n**Simple explanation:** An arduous task is not just difficult; it requires long, serious effort.\n**Memory hook:** **Arduous = hard uphill climb.**\n**GRE synonyms:** strenuous, laborious, onerous, taxing, demanding\n**Basic synonyms:** hard, difficult, tiring, challenging\n**Antonyms:** easy, effortless, simple, undemanding\n**Common usage:** arduous journey, arduous task, arduous training, arduous process\n**Confusing word:** **Arduous ≠ Ardent.** Arduous = difficult; ardent = passionate or enthusiastic.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. The hike was arduous.\n   Meaning: The hike was very difficult.\n   Bangla: হাঁটাটি কঠিন ছিল।\n\n2. Preparing for the exam was arduous.\n   Meaning: It required much effort.\n   Bangla: পরীক্ষার প্রস্তুতি শ্রমসাধ্য।\n\n3. The road to the village was arduous.\n   Meaning: The road was hard to travel.\n   Bangla: পথটি কষ্টকর।\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n4. The researchers faced the arduous task of collecting data from remote regions.\n   Meaning: The task required great effort.\n   Bangla: কঠিন তথ্য সংগ্রহ।\n\n5. The reform process was arduous because many institutions resisted change.\n   Meaning: Reform was difficult and slow.\n   Bangla: সংস্কার প্রক্রিয়া কঠিন ছিল।\n\n6. Writing a credible literature review can be arduous for new researchers.\n   Meaning: It needs patience and effort.\n   Bangla: সাহিত্য পর্যালোচনা শ্রমসাধ্য।\n\n7. The company survived an arduous restructuring after the financial crisis.\n   Meaning: The restructuring was difficult and demanding.\n   Bangla: কঠিন পুনর্গঠন।\n\n**Real-world / paper-style examples**\n\n8. In engineering design, validating a model under multiple conditions is often arduous.\n   Meaning: Testing across conditions takes serious effort.\n   Bangla: মডেল যাচাই কঠিন।\n\n9. In public health, vaccine distribution in remote areas can be arduous.\n   Meaning: Logistics are difficult.\n   Bangla: দূরবর্তী এলাকায় টিকা বিতরণ কঠিন।\n\n10. In field research, arduous terrain can limit data collection.\n    Meaning: Difficult land conditions slow research.\n    Bangla: কঠিন ভূখণ্ড গবেষণা বাধাগ্রস্ত করে।\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The rescue team began a **strenuous** climb.\n2. The translation required **laborious** attention to detail.\n3. The new regulation imposed **onerous** duties on small firms.\n4. The project was mentally **taxing**.\n5. The program placed **demanding** expectations on students.\n6. The athlete followed a **strenuous** training schedule.\n7. The historian completed a **laborious** review of old documents.\n8. The contract created **onerous** financial obligations.\n9. The debate was emotionally **taxing** for both sides.\n10. The job is **demanding** but rewarding.\n11. The mountain route was **strenuous**.\n12. Cleaning the corrupted data was **laborious**.\n13. The loan terms were **onerous** for poor borrowers.\n14. Long simulations can be computationally **taxing**.\n15. The professor assigned a **demanding** research paper.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Arduous = hard + effortful = পরিশ্রমসাধ্য**\n\n---",
