      "rawMarkdown": "# 67. Artless\n\n**Pronunciation:** ART-ləs\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Natural, sincere, and without deception; sometimes simple or naive.\n**Bangla meaning:** সরল, অকপট, নিষ্পাপ, কপটতাহীন\n**Root story:** Artless means “without artifice.” Here, “art” means clever trick or artificial skill. So artless = without trickery.\n**Simple explanation:** An artless person speaks or behaves simply and honestly, without trying to manipulate others.\n**Memory hook:** **Artless = no artificial trick = sincere.**\n**GRE synonyms:** guileless, naive, ingenuous, unaffected, innocent\n**Basic synonyms:** simple, honest, natural, sincere\n**Antonyms:** artful, cunning, crafty, deceitful, calculating\n**Common usage:** artless charm, artless honesty, artless smile, artless innocence\n**Confusing word:** **Artless ≠ Artful.** Artless = sincere/simple; artful = clever, crafty, sometimes deceptive.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. The child gave an artless smile.\n   Meaning: The smile was innocent and natural.\n   Bangla: সরল হাসি।\n\n2. Her artless answer touched everyone.\n   Meaning: Her answer was honest and simple.\n   Bangla: অকপট উত্তর।\n\n3. He spoke with artless honesty.\n   Meaning: He spoke without deception.\n   Bangla: কপটতাহীন সততা।\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n4. The witness’s artless manner made her testimony seem credible.\n   Meaning: Her simplicity made her believable.\n   Bangla: সরল আচরণ।\n\n5. The memoir’s power lies in its artless narration rather than polished style.\n   Meaning: The writing is sincere, not artificially decorated.\n   Bangla: অকৃত্রিম বর্ণনা।\n\n6. Critics praised the actor’s artless performance for its emotional authenticity.\n   Meaning: The performance felt natural.\n   Bangla: স্বাভাবিক অভিনয়।\n\n7. Although he appeared artless, he understood the politics of the office.\n   Meaning: He seemed naive but was not necessarily foolish.\n   Bangla: সরল মনে হলেও বুঝদার।\n\n**Real-world / paper-style examples**\n\n8. In literary criticism, artless prose can create a sense of honesty and intimacy.\n   Meaning: Simple writing may feel sincere.\n   Bangla: সরল গদ্য বিশ্বাসযোগ্য লাগে।\n\n9. In interviews, artless responses sometimes reveal more than prepared statements.\n   Meaning: Natural answers can be more revealing.\n   Bangla: অকপট উত্তর বেশি প্রকাশ করে।\n\n10. In leadership communication, artless sincerity may build trust better than scripted slogans.\n    Meaning: Natural honesty builds confidence.\n    Bangla: কপটতাহীন আন্তরিকতা বিশ্বাস আনে।\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. Her **guileless** expression suggested innocence.\n2. The young intern was **naive** about office politics.\n3. His **ingenuous** apology seemed sincere.\n4. The speaker’s **unaffected** style appealed to ordinary listeners.\n5. The child’s **innocent** question embarrassed the adults.\n6. A **guileless** person may trust too easily.\n7. His **naive** optimism ignored practical limits.\n8. The candidate’s **ingenuous** remarks sounded refreshing.\n9. Her **unaffected** manners made her popular.\n10. The witness appeared **innocent**, not calculated.\n11. His **guileless** honesty made deception unlikely.\n12. The plan was **naive** but morally appealing.\n13. The novel’s narrator is **ingenuous**, not cynical.\n14. The performance felt **unaffected** and sincere.\n15. The child’s **innocent** charm softened the room.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Artless = without trickery = সরল / অকপট**\n\n---",
