      "rawMarkdown": "# 69. Assuage\n\n**Pronunciation:** ə-SWAYJ\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To make an unpleasant feeling less intense; to soothe, ease, or relieve.\n**Bangla meaning:** প্রশমিত করা, উপশম করা, শান্ত করা\n**Root story:** From an old root idea connected with “softening” or “making sweet.” Imagine making pain or fear softer.\n**Simple explanation:** To assuage fear, pain, anger, guilt, or concern means to reduce it and make someone feel calmer.\n**Memory hook:** **Assuage = soothe the surge.**\n**GRE synonyms:** soothe, alleviate, mitigate, mollify, ease, pacify\n**Basic synonyms:** calm, comfort, reduce, relieve\n**Antonyms:** aggravate, intensify, provoke, exacerbate, worsen\n**Common usage:** assuage fears, assuage guilt, assuage pain, assuage concerns\n**Confusing word:** **Assuage ≠ Assume.** Assuage = reduce pain/fear; assume = suppose or take responsibility.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. Her words assuaged my fear.\n   Meaning: Her words made me less afraid.\n   Bangla: ভয় কমাল।\n\n2. Medicine assuaged the pain.\n   Meaning: Medicine reduced the pain.\n   Bangla: ব্যথা উপশম করল।\n\n3. He apologized to assuage his guilt.\n   Meaning: He wanted to feel less guilty.\n   Bangla: অপরাধবোধ কমাতে।\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n4. The mayor’s statement did little to assuage public concern.\n   Meaning: People remained worried.\n   Bangla: জনউদ্বেগ কমাতে ব্যর্থ।\n\n5. The company released safety data to assuage investors’ fears.\n   Meaning: The company tried to calm investors.\n   Bangla: বিনিয়োগকারীদের ভয় কমাতে।\n\n6. The charity campaign helped assuage criticism after the scandal.\n   Meaning: It reduced public criticism.\n   Bangla: সমালোচনা প্রশমিত করল।\n\n7. The policy was designed to assuage rural anger over rising prices.\n   Meaning: It aimed to calm anger.\n   Bangla: গ্রামীণ ক্ষোভ কমানো।\n\n**Real-world / paper-style examples**\n\n8. In public health communication, transparent data can assuage fear during outbreaks.\n   Meaning: Clear information reduces panic.\n   Bangla: স্বচ্ছ তথ্য ভয় কমায়।\n\n9. In environmental policy, compensation programs may assuage local resistance to conservation projects.\n   Meaning: Compensation can reduce opposition.\n   Bangla: ক্ষতিপূরণ বিরোধিতা কমায়।\n\n10. In psychology, social support can assuage anxiety after traumatic events.\n    Meaning: Support can relieve emotional distress.\n    Bangla: সহায়তা উদ্বেগ কমায়।\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The nurse tried to **soothe** the frightened child.\n2. The new drug helped **alleviate** chronic pain.\n3. The law was intended to **mitigate** economic hardship.\n4. The manager tried to **mollify** angry customers.\n5. Rest can **ease** muscle tension.\n6. The negotiator attempted to **pacify** the crowd.\n7. Soft music helped **soothe** her anxiety.\n8. Better infrastructure may **alleviate** traffic congestion.\n9. Emergency aid can **mitigate** the effects of famine.\n10. The apology failed to **mollify** the critics.\n11. The counselor helped **ease** his guilt.\n12. The treaty helped **pacify** the border region.\n13. Warm tea can **soothe** a sore throat.\n14. The program aims to **alleviate** poverty.\n15. Careful planning can **mitigate** risk.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Assuage = reduce pain/fear/anger = প্রশমিত করা**\n\n---",
