      "rawMarkdown": "# 70. Betray\n\n**Pronunciation:** bih-TRAY\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To be disloyal; to reveal secrets; or to unintentionally show a feeling.\n**Bangla meaning:** বিশ্বাসঘাতকতা করা, ফাঁস করা, প্রকাশ করে ফেলা\n**Root story:** Related to Latin **tradere**, meaning “to hand over.” Betray originally carries the idea of handing someone over to an enemy.\n**Simple explanation:** Betray can mean breaking trust, revealing secret information, or showing a hidden emotion.\n**Memory hook:** **Betray = break trust or reveal hidden truth.**\n**GRE synonyms:** reveal, expose, disclose, divulge, deceive, be disloyal\n**Basic synonyms:** show, leak, cheat, turn against\n**Antonyms:** protect, conceal, hide, support, remain loyal\n**Common usage:** betray a friend, betray a secret, betray emotion, betray anxiety\n**Confusing word:** **Betray ≠ Belie.** Betray can reveal a hidden truth; belie gives a false impression or contradicts.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. He betrayed his friend.\n   Meaning: He broke his friend’s trust.\n   Bangla: বন্ধুর সঙ্গে বিশ্বাসঘাতকতা করল।\n\n2. She betrayed the secret.\n   Meaning: She revealed the secret.\n   Bangla: গোপন কথা ফাঁস করল।\n\n3. His voice betrayed fear.\n   Meaning: His voice showed fear.\n   Bangla: কণ্ঠে ভয় প্রকাশ পেল।\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n4. The official betrayed public trust by selling confidential information.\n   Meaning: He acted disloyally.\n   Bangla: জনবিশ্বাস ভঙ্গ করল।\n\n5. The calm report betrayed little of the crisis behind the scenes.\n   Meaning: It revealed very little.\n   Bangla: ভেতরের সংকট প্রকাশ করেনি।\n\n6. Her hesitation betrayed uncertainty despite her confident words.\n   Meaning: Her pause revealed doubt.\n   Bangla: দ্বিধা সন্দেহ প্রকাশ করল।\n\n7. The leaked emails betrayed a pattern of deliberate deception.\n   Meaning: They revealed dishonesty.\n   Bangla: প্রতারণা প্রকাশ করল।\n\n**Real-world / paper-style examples**\n\n8. In diplomatic history, spies often betrayed state secrets to foreign powers.\n   Meaning: They revealed confidential information.\n   Bangla: রাষ্ট্রীয় গোপনীয়তা ফাঁস।\n\n9. In literary analysis, a character’s small gesture may betray hidden guilt.\n   Meaning: The gesture reveals inner emotion.\n   Bangla: অঙ্গভঙ্গি অপরাধবোধ প্রকাশ করে।\n\n10. In research ethics, manipulating data betrays the basic trust of scientific inquiry.\n    Meaning: It violates research integrity.\n    Bangla: গবেষণার বিশ্বাস ভঙ্গ করে।\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The documents **revealed** systematic corruption.\n2. The investigation **exposed** hidden financial abuse.\n3. The report **disclosed** the company’s losses.\n4. The witness refused to **divulge** confidential names.\n5. The agent **deceived** his own organization.\n6. He was **disloyal** to those who trusted him.\n7. The data **revealed** an unexpected pattern.\n8. The camera **exposed** the fraud.\n9. The committee **disclosed** the results publicly.\n10. The journalist would not **divulge** her source.\n11. The false promise **deceived** many voters.\n12. His actions proved he was **disloyal**.\n13. Her nervous smile **revealed** her anxiety.\n14. The audit **exposed** accounting irregularities.\n15. The files **disclosed** serious safety failures.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Betray = break trust or reveal hidden truth = বিশ্বাসঘাতকতা / প্রকাশ করা**\n\n---",
