      "rawMarkdown": "# 77. Coalesce\n\n**Pronunciation:** koh-uh-LES\n**Part of speech:** Verb\n**Core meaning:** To come together and form one whole.\n**Bangla meaning:** একত্রিত হওয়া, মিলে যাওয়া, সংযুক্ত হওয়া\n**Root story:** From Latin **co-** = together + a root related to growing. So coalesce originally suggests separate things growing together into one body.\n**Simple explanation:** When groups, ideas, particles, plans, or movements coalesce, they combine into a single stronger unit.\n**Memory hook:** **Coalesce = collect into one.**\n**GRE synonyms:** merge, fuse, unite, combine, consolidate, amalgamate\n**Basic synonyms:** join, come together, blend, gather\n**Antonyms:** separate, divide, split, disperse, fragment\n**Common usage:** ideas coalesce, factions coalesce, particles coalesce, movements coalesce\n**Confusing word:** **Coalesce ≠ Collapse.** Coalesce = come together; collapse = fall down or fail.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. The small groups coalesced into one team.\n2. Drops of water coalesced on the glass.\n3. Their ideas slowly coalesced into a clear plan.\n\n**Medium examples**\n\n4. Several local protests coalesced into a national movement.\n5. The committee’s scattered suggestions coalesced into a practical reform package.\n6. Political factions coalesced around a single candidate.\n7. Over time, individual complaints coalesced into a serious public controversy.\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n8. In materials science, tiny particles may coalesce into larger clusters under specific thermal conditions.\n9. In sociology, shared grievances can coalesce into collective action.\n10. The researcher’s preliminary observations eventually coalesced into a coherent theory.\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The two firms decided to **merge**.\n2. Hydrogen atoms **fuse** under extreme pressure in stars.\n3. The crisis helped **unite** rival political groups.\n4. The software can **combine** multiple data sets.\n5. The reform sought to **consolidate** several agencies.\n6. The two cultures began to **amalgamate** over generations.\n7. Small banks may **merge** to survive competition.\n8. The metal surfaces **fused** under intense heat.\n9. The leader tried to **unite** the divided community.\n10. Researchers **combined** survey data with interview evidence.\n11. The company **consolidated** its regional offices.\n12. The new policy attempted to **amalgamate** different welfare programs.\n13. The fragments slowly **merged** into one narrative.\n14. The opposition parties **united** before the election.\n15. The departments were **consolidated** to reduce cost.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Coalesce = separate things become one = একত্রিত হওয়া**\n\n---",
