      "rawMarkdown": "# 78. Cogent\n\n**Pronunciation:** KOH-jənt\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Clear, logical, and convincing.\n**Bangla meaning:** যুক্তিসঙ্গত, দৃঢ়প্রত্যয়ী, বিশ্বাসযোগ্য\n**Root story:** From Latin **cogere**, meaning “to drive together” or “to compel.” A cogent argument “compels” belief because its logic is strong.\n**Simple explanation:** A cogent argument is not emotional noise. It is clear, well-organized, evidence-based, and persuasive.\n**Memory hook:** **Cogent = convincing logic.**\n**GRE synonyms:** convincing, persuasive, compelling, sound, forceful, valid\n**Basic synonyms:** logical, clear, strong, reasonable\n**Antonyms:** weak, illogical, unconvincing, flawed, specious\n**Common usage:** cogent argument, cogent analysis, cogent explanation, cogent evidence\n**Confusing word:** **Cogent ≠ Coherent.** Coherent = understandable and connected; cogent = logically persuasive.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. She gave a cogent answer.\n2. His argument was cogent and clear.\n3. The judge accepted the cogent explanation.\n\n**Medium examples**\n\n4. The proposal became more cogent after the author added evidence.\n5. The professor praised the student’s cogent analysis of the poem.\n6. A cogent policy paper must connect claims with data.\n7. The lawyer’s cogent reasoning weakened the opponent’s case.\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n8. The study offers a cogent explanation for why rural adoption of renewable energy remains slow.\n9. Although the theory is controversial, its internal logic is unusually cogent.\n10. The reviewer rejected the manuscript because its central claim lacked cogent empirical support.\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The evidence was highly **convincing**.\n2. Her speech was calm but **persuasive**.\n3. The documentary made a **compelling** case for reform.\n4. The conclusion was based on **sound** reasoning.\n5. The lawyer made a **forceful** argument.\n6. The model produced a **valid** interpretation of the data.\n7. The witness gave a **convincing** account.\n8. The article was **persuasive** because it used strong evidence.\n9. His objection was **compelling**, not merely emotional.\n10. The engineer offered a **sound** technical explanation.\n11. The editorial presented a **forceful** critique.\n12. The result is **valid** only under controlled conditions.\n13. The experiment gave **convincing** support to the hypothesis.\n14. The committee found her reasoning **persuasive**.\n15. A **sound** argument survives criticism.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Cogent = logically convincing = যুক্তিসঙ্গত ও বিশ্বাসযোগ্য**\n\n---",
