      "rawMarkdown": "# 79. Compelling\n\n**Pronunciation:** kəm-PEL-ing\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Strongly convincing, powerful, or attracting attention.\n**Bangla meaning:** জোরালো, আকর্ষণীয়, বিশ্বাস করাতে বাধ্য করে এমন\n**Root story:** From Latin **com-** = together + **pellere** = to drive. Compelling literally suggests something that “drives” your mind toward belief or attention.\n**Simple explanation:** Something compelling is so strong, interesting, or persuasive that you cannot easily ignore it.\n**Memory hook:** **Compelling = pulls/forces attention.**\n**GRE synonyms:** persuasive, convincing, cogent, gripping, powerful, irresistible\n**Basic synonyms:** strong, interesting, attractive, forceful\n**Antonyms:** weak, dull, unconvincing, boring, forgettable\n**Common usage:** compelling evidence, compelling story, compelling reason, compelling argument\n**Confusing word:** **Compelling ≠ Compelled.** Compelling = persuasive/interesting; compelled = forced.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. The story was compelling.\n2. She gave a compelling reason for leaving.\n3. The evidence was compelling enough to change his mind.\n\n**Medium examples**\n\n4. The documentary was compelling because it combined personal stories with hard data.\n5. The researcher presented compelling evidence that air pollution affects child health.\n6. A compelling speech can move people without exaggeration.\n7. The court found the witness’s testimony compelling.\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n8. The paper’s most compelling contribution is its careful comparison of competing models.\n9. Although the hypothesis is attractive, the evidence supporting it is not yet compelling.\n10. The report makes a compelling case for redesigning urban transport systems.\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. Her argument was deeply **persuasive**.\n2. The results were **convincing** but not final.\n3. The professor gave a **cogent** explanation.\n4. The novel’s opening chapter was **gripping**.\n5. The speech had a **powerful** emotional effect.\n6. The offer was almost **irresistible**.\n7. The data made the conclusion **persuasive**.\n8. The experiment produced **convincing** evidence.\n9. The essay became more **cogent** after revision.\n10. The film was **gripping** from beginning to end.\n11. The image had a **powerful** symbolic meaning.\n12. The argument was **irresistible** because every objection had been answered.\n13. The presentation was **persuasive** without being aggressive.\n14. The witness gave a **convincing** timeline.\n15. The article offered a **powerful** critique of inequality.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Compelling = too strong to ignore = জোরালো / আকর্ষণীয়**\n\n---",
