      "rawMarkdown": "# 82. Cosmopolitan\n\n**Pronunciation:** koz-muh-POL-uh-tən\n**Part of speech:** Adjective / Noun\n**Core meaning:** Familiar with and comfortable in many cultures; global and worldly.\n**Bangla meaning:** বিশ্বজনীন, আন্তর্জাতিক, বহু সংস্কৃতিমনা, নাগরিক\n**Root story:** From Greek **kosmos** = world + **polites** = citizen. Cosmopolitan literally means “citizen of the world.”\n**Simple explanation:** A cosmopolitan person, city, or attitude is open to many cultures, languages, foods, ideas, and ways of life.\n**Memory hook:** **Cosmopolitan = citizen of the cosmos/world.**\n**GRE synonyms:** worldly, sophisticated, international, urbane, multicultural\n**Basic synonyms:** global, cultured, open-minded, modern\n**Antonyms:** provincial, narrow-minded, parochial, insular\n**Common usage:** cosmopolitan city, cosmopolitan outlook, cosmopolitan culture, cosmopolitan lifestyle\n**Confusing word:** **Cosmopolitan ≠ Cosmology.** Cosmopolitan = global/cultured; cosmology = study of the universe.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. London is a cosmopolitan city.\n2. She has a cosmopolitan outlook.\n3. The restaurant has a cosmopolitan menu.\n\n**Medium examples**\n\n4. A cosmopolitan education exposes students to different cultures and ideas.\n5. The city became more cosmopolitan as immigrants, tourists, and investors arrived.\n6. His cosmopolitan manners made him comfortable in almost any country.\n7. The magazine targets cosmopolitan readers interested in global trends.\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n8. The novel contrasts cosmopolitan tolerance with provincial suspicion.\n9. In migration studies, cosmopolitan identity often emerges from cross-cultural contact.\n10. The university promoted a cosmopolitan curriculum that included global history, ethics, and languages.\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. She has a **worldly** understanding of politics.\n2. His taste in art is unusually **sophisticated**.\n3. The conference attracted an **international** audience.\n4. The diplomat’s **urbane** manner impressed everyone.\n5. The school promotes a **multicultural** environment.\n6. A **worldly** traveler rarely fears difference.\n7. The essay was written in a **sophisticated** style.\n8. The company expanded into **international** markets.\n9. His **urbane** wit made him popular in elite circles.\n10. **Multicultural** classrooms can broaden student perspectives.\n11. Her **worldly** experience shaped her political views.\n12. The design was modern and **sophisticated**.\n13. The festival had an **international** character.\n14. The host was polished and **urbane**.\n15. The city’s **multicultural** life influenced its cuisine.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Cosmopolitan = citizen-of-the-world mindset = বিশ্বজনীন / আন্তর্জাতিক**\n\n---",
