      "rawMarkdown": "# 85. Diffident\n\n**Pronunciation:** DIF-i-dənt\n**Part of speech:** Adjective\n**Core meaning:** Lacking self-confidence; shy and hesitant.\n**Bangla meaning:** আত্মবিশ্বাসহীন, লাজুক, সংকোচপূর্ণ\n**Root story:** From Latin **dis-** = away + **fidere** = to trust. Diffident literally suggests “not trusting oneself.”\n**Simple explanation:** A diffident person may have ability, but they hesitate because they do not feel confident.\n**Memory hook:** **Diffident = difficult to feel confident.**\n**GRE synonyms:** timid, shy, insecure, hesitant, bashful, self-effacing\n**Basic synonyms:** nervous, unsure, quiet, reserved\n**Antonyms:** confident, bold, assertive, self-assured, audacious\n**Common usage:** diffident student, diffident smile, diffident manner, diffident speaker\n**Confusing word:** **Diffident ≠ Different.** Diffident = shy/lacking confidence; different = not the same.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Easy examples**\n\n1. The diffident student rarely raised his hand.\n2. She gave a diffident smile.\n3. He sounded diffident during the interview.\n\n**Medium examples**\n\n4. Although talented, she remained diffident about presenting her research.\n5. A diffident leader may struggle to make unpopular but necessary decisions.\n6. His diffident manner made people underestimate his intelligence.\n7. The teacher encouraged diffident students to speak in small groups first.\n\n**GRE / Academic examples**\n\n8. The author’s early essays are marked by a diffident tone, unlike the confidence of her later work.\n9. In classroom studies, diffident learners may know the answer but avoid public participation.\n10. The researcher was diffident about drawing broad conclusions from a small sample.\n\n## GRE synonym examples\n\n1. The child was too **timid** to speak.\n2. She felt **shy** around strangers.\n3. His **insecure** tone weakened the presentation.\n4. The intern was **hesitant** to challenge the manager.\n5. The actor gave a **bashful** smile.\n6. His **self-effacing** style made him seem humble.\n7. A **timid** response can be mistaken for ignorance.\n8. The new student was **shy** but observant.\n9. She felt **insecure** about her pronunciation.\n10. The committee was **hesitant** to approve the risky plan.\n11. He looked **bashful** after the compliment.\n12. Her **self-effacing** humor made the audience comfortable.\n13. A **timid** investor may avoid profitable risks.\n14. He became less **hesitant** after practice.\n15. The speaker’s **insecure** delivery hid a strong argument.\n\n**Final memory line:** **Diffident = not confident = আত্মবিশ্বাসহীন / লাজুক**\n\n---",
